This project has a graphify knowledge graph at graphify-out/. It indexes **this repo only**, not the Obsidian vault.

**Layering (north star: discover → verify → price → execute):**
- Paperclip — current task and ship comments
- Obsidian (`~/ai-agent-stack/obsidian-vault`, `MADSAN_BRAIN.md`) — dossiers, data-source tiers, ADRs, runbooks
- graphify — where in code; see `docs/AGENT_KNOWLEDGE_LAYERS.md` and vault note `09_Technical-Architecture/Meridian code navigation (graphify).md`

- For codebase or architecture questions, when `graphify-out/graph.json` exists, first run `graphify query "<question>"` (or `graphify path "<A>" "<B>"` / `graphify explain "<concept>"`). These return a scoped subgraph, usually much smaller than `GRAPH_REPORT.md` or raw grep output.
- Before coding on Paperclip tasks: skim Obsidian folders named in the issue (`08_Data-Sources/`, `06_Company-Dossiers/`, `12_Decisions/`) then graphify-query the acceptance criteria.
- If graphify-out/wiki/index.md exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files
- Read graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md only for broad architecture review or when query/path/explain do not surface enough context
- After modifying code files in this session, run `graphify update .` to keep the graph current (AST-only, no API cost)
- Reusable policy/ops findings after ship → Obsidian (`12_Decisions/`, `10_Runbooks/`, `08_Data-Sources/`), not graphify
